The paper discusses consistency of multi-view models in UML and OCL, which are both modeling languages used in software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also mentions the use of Distributed Ontology, Model and Specification Language (DOL), which falls under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the use of logic and transformation techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.SD (Software Development). Finally, the paper mentions the use of universal logic, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
